<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000019#     2#          128#">Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-128</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_19.2-128"/><heading><desig>§ 19.2-128.</desig><title>Penalties for failure to appear</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Whoever, having been released pursuant to this chapter or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-319"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-319">§ 19.2-319<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#          319#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or on a summons pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-73"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-73">§ 19.2-73<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#           73#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-74"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-74">§ 19.2-74<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#           74#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, willfully fails to appear before any court or judicial officer as required, shall, after notice to all interested parties, incur a forfeiture of any security which may have been given or pledged for his release, unless one of the parties can show good cause for excusing the absence, or unless the court, in its sound discretion, shall determine that neither the interests of justice nor the power of the court to conduct orderly proceedings will be served by such forfeiture.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Any person (i) charged with a felony offense or (ii) convicted of a felony offense and execution of sentence is suspended pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-319"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-319">§ 19.2-319<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#          319#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> who willfully fails to appear before any court as required shall be guilty of a Class 6 felony.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Any person (i) charged with a misdemeanor offense or (ii) convicted of a misdemeanor offense and execution of sentence is suspended pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-319"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-319">§ 19.2-319<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#          319#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> who willfully fails to appear before any court as required shall be guilty of a Class 1 misdemeanor.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 19.1-109.7; 1973, c. 485; 1975, c. 495; 1981, c. 382; 1982, c. 271; <citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 821"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 821">1999, c. 821<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#000821#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PST0-004G-K06M-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 19.2.</desig><title>CRIMINAL PROCEDURE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 9.</desig><title>BAIL AND RECOGNIZANCES</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 1.</desig><title>BAIL</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Criminal Law &amp; Procedure</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NEU0RkE1OUQwNUQwNDgxODhEODZCMjkzOTg3NThBNzk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Elements</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RDc2NEEyRUY2M0M4NEY4N0JCREFDQTZDMTZFMDg1MkM7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MEY5OUNGQUZFRTQxNDVDMTk1QjY5RUY1RDBEODhGRkY</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MTY4MEE3MTQyREY0NDNDRUE3OTlDMkJGNDVDM0NFMjc7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MEY5OUNGQUZFRTQxNDVDMTk1QjY5RUY1RDBEODhGRkY</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Judicial Discretion</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RjZFQkExMjgxODRCNDZCNDhDOTkwNzY2NUVCNjg3NDA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MEUzMkE2MTZCMThENDAwNDhCM0I4RDA2OURFRDAwNDI</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Proceedings</className><clas